-- Credit Suisse Sent Names to U.S. to Avoid Charges, Le Temps Says
-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m
-- 2012-07-20T22:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-20/credit-suisse-sent-names-to-u-s-to-avoid-charges-le-temps-says.html
Credit Suisse Group AG transferred
documents and emails containing employee names to the U.S.
authorities, reducing the risk of the U.S. initiating
prosecutions,  Le Temps  reported, citing an interview with Chief
Executive Officer  Brady Dougan .  Dougan declined to provide the number of names handed over,
the Swiss newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Giles Broom in Geneva at 
 gbroom@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at 
 fconnelly@bloomberg.net  